snippet: A Greek Revival townhouse in Greenwich Village with a classic brownstone stoop was the sale of the week.
abstract: Big Ticket column; four story red-brick Greek Revival townhouse at 24 West 11th Street in Greenwich Village is highest residential sale of week in New York City, closing at $19.25 million.
lead_paragraph: A Greek Revival townhouse in Greenwich Village with a classic brownstone stoop was the sale of the week.

headline.main: For $19.25 Million, a Greenwich Village Classic
